Chilean Stocks: Cap, Cencosud, Concha y Toro, La Polar, Vapores

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-02-28T21:19:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/chilean-stocks-cencosud-concha-y-toro-lan-airlines-la-polar.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:10 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose 1.6 percent to 4,444.57.    Cap SA  (CAP CC),  Chile ’s largest steel producer and iron
miner, led gains among members of the IPSA index with a 3.9
percent rise to 22,667 pesos, its largest increase in more than
six weeks. The company rose in line with base metal prices, as
improving economic data buoyed demand expectations.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD CC) climbed 1.3 percent to 3,232.2
pesos, its highest price in almost two weeks. Chile’s largest
retailer by sales was mentioned as a “top-pick” at Banchile-
Citi.  Cia. Sudamericana de Vapores SA (VAPORES CC) fell 3.8
percent to 374.99 pesos. Latin America’s largest container
shipping company has lost 11 percent since Feb. 24, when it
reported full year and quarterly results below analysts’
estimates.    Empresas La Polar SA  (LAPOLAR CC) rose for a third day,
gaining 2 percent to 2,767.3 pesos. The department-store
operator is one of Banchile-Citi’s top picks among Chilean
retailers, analysts including Peter McMenamin and Celso Sanchez
wrote in an e-mailed note to clients.    Vina Concha y Toro SA  (CONCHA CC) rose 1 percent to 995.97
pesos after three days of losses. Chile’s largest wine exporter
reported fourth-quarter earnings that met expectations, Banco de
Chile’s brokerage unit wrote in an e-mailed note to clients.  To contact the reporter on this story:
